"I am well aware of the efforts of the staff to keep our prison system functioning and to modernize it", the Minister of Justice said in the letter.
"I have instructed the management of the prison to take immediate action to ensure that a situation such as this, which has arisen from a lack of assessment of the overtime available, does not recur in the future", added Ms Alliot-Marie.
The December wage is therefore low, except for the management staff, who enjoy high service and target bonuses, explains UFAP/UNSA, for whom the "budget constraints" must be justified.
"This is an absolute scandal", the interregional trade union FO in Marseille is outraged and announces that it will boycott "all meetings and convocations" until further orders are given.
