The unions say that the situation is not the same in all regions, with some less affected than others.
But in any case, it is wrong, says UFAP Secretary-General Jean-François Forget.
Obama thinks he always gives out better presents at Christmas than he gets himself.
U.S. President Barack Obama, who will spend Christmas with his family for the first time at the White House, has told talk show host Oprah Winfrey that he always gives out better gifts than he receives.
In a Sunday evening ABC special, the president and his wife, Michelle, gave a glimpse of how they will spend the holidays in their new, stately home.
Even Bo, the family's little four-legged companion, will be joining the party.
"Santa Claus loves Bo too", Michelle Obama reiterates, adding that the dog will of course also get a gift.
Michelle Obama vehemently denied her husband's claims about the quality of the gifts. "I gave you beautiful gifts last year", she teases the president.
