He also recalled that the Competitiveness Plan, which is part of the Automotive Industry Integrated Plan (PIA), has provided EUR 800 million for projects by 19 vehicle manufacturers and 137 suppliers, which in turn have led to investments of more than EUR 3 billion.
The Prime Minister explained that these investments are intended both for the development of new models and for the modernisation of existing products and processes.
Mr Zapatero also underlined the measures taken by the Government to stimulate demand, in reference to Plan 2000E, which are being implemented in cooperation with the Autonomous Communities and the car manufacturers.
