It is quite the opposite: it has been a long time since we have tested such a small and light model, which at the same time gives you a great sense of safety in the corners, even at high speed.
He's a small athlete, able to warm up his muscles at a low speed for the time required, until we give him the commands to race, to brake, to recover, and then to get everything out of his engine again...
It does everything you tell it to do, and the car does everything you tell it to do with your hands on the wheel, thanks to its steering, which is as communicative as it is precise.
