How much should you earn from your Facebook profile?
Facebook users can now find out what their salary is, based on their profile, thanks to the new application Trovit, the search engine with the most ads for real estate, job offers and cars in Spain.
The "How much should you earn?" tool calculates users' salaries based on more than 140,000 job offers available at Trovit in Spain. Users can use a Facebook form to enter their occupation, work experience, age and the city where they work.
Just one week after the application was first made available, the search engine found that the Spanish worker on average "feels badly paid", explains Trovit product manager Albert Ribera in a press release.
The Spanish are the worst paid according to the data available to Trovit through its search engines in the UK and France.
A British programmer earns a gross annual salary of 45,226 euros and a Frenchman 31,059, as opposed to the 24,000 euros earned by a Spaniard.
As a result, a truck driver has an annual net salary of EUR 34,247 in England, EUR 25,751 in France and EUR 16,420 in Spain.
According to Trovit, the worst paid job in Spain is that of a waiter with 11,592 euros net per year, followed by that of a salesman with 14,725 euros and that of a worker with 15,667 euros.
The most searched jobs on the Internet in the last three months are those of a driver, part-time jobs and social workers.
