The third and last consortium, which is in the short list, is called LBRJV, formed by the capital of the Australian Leighton (a subsidiary of the German construction company Hochtief, which in turn belongs to ACS), the local Baulderstone (owned by the German group Bilfinger Berger) and the French company Razel, which specialises in public works.
The Australian infrastructure market offers huge construction and privatisation opportunities, but there is a barrier to be overcome, as access is only possible by buying a local construction company.
