Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps:identification of the vehicle, finding the spare part, and creating and preparing a cost estimate.
The ease of use of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince the older professionals, who are usually more or less against the use of these new computer techniques.
The database contains 1,034 vehicles, of which 666 are motor vehicles, 109 are off-road vehicles, 137 are motorcycles, 78 are small vans and 44 are trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with an Internet connection to use it.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by the chassis number, a graphic of the model concerned appears and the spare part required is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the hours worked, surcharges or discounts, and then print out the estimate of the costs and pass it on to his customers.
AudaTaller is not, however, a review tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented one does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros per year, an amount which the customer can easily pay.
Audatex is currently working on the possibility of offering these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that has been waiting for a long time in the automotive industry, because it allows you to choose a door, for example, and then turn the image completely around to look inside.
